

# To view a file:
groff -man -Tascii file.1


# To specify a manpath:
man -M $MANPATH file # MANPATH is colon separated list
# eg: to view the file /p/a/t/h/share/man/man1/foo.1, do
# man -M /p/a/t/h/share/man foo


# Common options:
-w      Display the location of the manual page instead of the contents of the manual page.
